The course is divided into three parts:
* An overview of the terminology and the formation of cultural policies after World War II;
* cultural management system, and cultural policy fundamentals in Estonia;
* discussions on cultural policies' development.
All parts are composed mainly of academic lectures and reading as well as discussions and group work.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course introduces the cultural policy models in Europe and Estonia. Overview of the political aspects of supporting national culture. Detailed analysis of fundementals of Estonian cultural policy.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  As a result of the course, the student will: - get definitions, terminology and a framework for understanding the cultural policies; - get an overview of cultural policies and developments after World War II; - get an ability to relate organization's culture or the culture of a particular project's to cultural policies; - get ability to formulate certain basic principles of political culture
